76561198000542458,Recommended,253630,8370348,"Posted: 28 December, 2013",all,mikeygiom,"Played about an hour so far and progressed through the tutorial and first 5 levels of the game, but at this stage I think that's all that is necessary to review. Nice pixel-art style graphics and a well chosen score set the mood for this broody journey through a space ship taken over by killer robots! If you are looking for story it seems that's all you're getting, but the gameplay is so engrossing you'll forget that pretty quickly! Add in the fact that once your squad members die they're really gone for good and a wiped out squad means game over and it's really easy to get pulled into this game. Fiendish difficulty and a steep learning curve help to keep you forever on your toes whilst playing.As far as the early access goes it seems to be a fully functional game, with a lot of room for expansion. For example there are currently 4 possible squad member classes (that cover quite a range of skills), maybe half a dozen item drops (but the varied effects show that there could be many more yet to come), and from what I've seen a small selection of enemies with pretty basic AI. That said I think this Alpha will probably entertain me for at least a couple more hours (especially if the difficulty keeps ramping up as it has been). I imagine the beta and full release will have many hours of gameplay due to the procedurally generated levels and possible squad configurations and tactics.My only gripe so far is with the control scheme and UI which sometimes make it difficult to work out exactly where you're at (which squad member you're controlling, ammo, etc) and makes it all to easy to make costly mistakes. It would be nice to see some refinement in this over the next few builds as it slows you down in a game that is already requiring a lot of thought before each move.I would definitely recommend, especially at it's current low price, currently very good, only going to get better :)"
