76561197981966854,Recommended,253630,12030517,"Posted: 8 September, 2014",all,rhoak,"This is a hard game to review. At first it can seem overly simplistic and somewhat uninspired. In reality this is the difficulty of the game trying to force the player to have some ambition, to get into the feel of a roguelike where you trying to fight your way out of a dire situation. For example, in the earlier stages of the game there is some confusion as to whether you should take out the enemy robots or just run for the nearest elevator with minimal losses but no gained experience. At first this seemed like a design flaw, but after multiple playthroughs I'm of the opinion that the designers want an authentic roguelike experience, they don't want a corridor roguelike where you're just blasing through enemies to get to the randomized item at the end of the level. Thus I appreciate the game so far and need to put more time into it (that is the goal of an good indie game right?)."
