,Recommended,253630,8355926,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,LandStander,"This is one game well worth the (cheap) price of Early Access.Loosely based on the Warhammer 40,000: Space Hulk board game, Steam Marines gives you 4 marines in a ruined steam-punk spaceship, tasked with reaching the elevator to the next level amid a swarm of angry robots.  The game works on a turn-based system with action points that players of XCOM will be very familiar with.  Once you've exhausted the action points on each marine, your turn ends, and all nearby robots get to spend their own action points to move or attack.Marines can move, attack, activate consoles, pick up loot (and believe me, you'll need a lot of it to survive), guard certain fire zones, or even bash down walls to create new paths.  Destructible environments make this a very dynamic game where you're never safe from the impending march of the machines.  Robots WILL come bursting out of the nearest wall when you're least expecting them - ruining your most careful positioning.  And positioning does matter quite a lot, particularly with some enemy types that are shielded from the front, forcing you to split your forces and flank.  Randomly generated levels provides endless replayability to perfect and level up your squad.I could go on about this game, but for how cheap it is, and much more is yet to come (it's only in alpha and already a blast to play), this is a no-brainer.  For gaes like it, take a look at Bionic Dues, XCOM, or Space Hulk."
