76561198042257165,Recommended,253630,19424402,"Posted: 1 December, 2015",all,clovrien,"If you're into solving near-impossible puzzles, then this is for you.In the beginning, i.e. after the tutorial and first few games, you will just die, die and die.You won't know what to do with the things you find, no instructions.  You won't know what will blow up in your face or not.  You won't know which ""monsters"" are immune to frontal damage.  You won't know which of your guys to shoot and when to shoot.So, you'll just die and die, however, you'll slowly begin to figure out how to put it together...then you'll die some more.After your first 30 games or so, don't worry - they don't take long, you'll start to get past the first couple of levels, sometimes.  Every time you start to make some progress...you guessed it...you'll die.Eventually, you'll start to move carefully, coordinate your squad, not over-extend, find some good stuff and know how to use it.  You'll get several levels completed, i.e. find the elevator, and just when you feel like you'll reach the goal...you'll die.  Did I mention this is all on ""normal"" difficulty; there are two levels of higher difficulty if you really like to die.You'll love this game if you HAVE TO FIGURE a way to win, no matter how painful.  If you're looking for a point and shoot, boss fight, make progress game...this isn't it.  This is for you those guys who love to beat impossible games."
